Thierry Breton, the European Industry Commissioner, proposes that EU countries jointly buy weapons from European companies to increase their production capacity. In addition, the US should help with purchases from US arms companies.

Breton aims to double the budget contribution for defense equipment to 3 billion euros. The proposals must be approved by EU governments, the European Parliament and NATO.

As a CDU member, I still wonder why our party itself is so populist in its opposition to the minimum wage. 
If work has to be worthwhile and you want to renew the promise of advancement, then you can't just look at the wage gap compared to the citizen's allowance.

A strange coincidence that we can see in the headlines these days: While the southwest of Germany is battling #flooding after heavy rain, activists from Last Generation are shutting down Munich Airport. And what is angering politicians? Of course, the action of the activists, who essentially want to remind the federal government that it is violating the legally established #climate protection goals. The very same federal government that has already been reprimanded by the EU for doing too little to combat the climate crisis.

Let's pause for a moment: What are we expecting of the younger generation? Across all parties, they are being demanded to work more in order to "secure" "prosperity". Without even once clarifying whether we all mean the same thing by "#prosperity". And as if you could secure something that no one even knows whether they mean the same thing. By the way: It always sounds like prosperity, as older people once defined it for themselves in the 1980s/90s. Even in this partial debate, it becomes clear what role young people are supposed to play: vicarious agents.

During the pandemic, they had to make many sacrifices for the elderly, now they are supposed to work (at least!) until they are 70 years old, and are also likely to be forced back into military service because war has become more likely. And when they then go into #retirement, it is hardly attractive if they have not made private provisions.

In return, they get broken infrastructure because no investment has been made in the #budget for decades because of the black zero fetish. A climate crisis that is causing crop failures, water shortages and distribution struggles. And a social welfare system (#pensions, #health, #care) that no longer provides adequately.

And then these young people are told: "Be yourself" - in order to unleash hatred and #incitement on them when they then take it literally and admit to their #homosexuality. Or to their vegan food. Or to stand up for their bodies. Or to their home country, which is not Germany.

What is this â€œprosperityâ€ again?

Das ist aber falsch. Es wÃ¤r so, als wÃ¼rde ein Zahnarzt eine OP am offenen Herzen ausfÃ¼hren. Doch die Rahmenbedingungen wurden immer schlechter, dass immer mehr die Branche verlassen haben. KommentarENG: Many people only remember Ms von der Leyen for how she ruined defence policy. Before that, she ruined the Landschaf day-care centre with the legal right to a childcare place in 2013. I have been a day-care centre manager for 20 years and unfortunately had to witness this process. Ms von der Leyen thought it would be enough to build more day-care centres. But she completely forgot that staff were also needed. At the time, I was volunteering for an association for Catholic day-care centres and was therefore close to the situation. I can still see the frustrated faces of the representatives from many other associations (AWO, Red Cross, etc.) who repeatedly pointed this out in meetings about the legal right but were not listened to by Ms von der Leyen. In practice: the groups got bigger, and Ms von der Leyen did not even consider the costs of training staff because she was of the opinion that nursery children were just like day-care centre children. But that is wrong. It would be like a dentist performing open-heart surgery. Nursery teachers belong to the professional group that most often undertakes further training because they want to do a good job and pay for it themselves despite the low salary. But the general conditions have become increasingly worse, so that more and more people have left the industry. Dear parents, no, if you are standing in front of closed facilities or have to pick up your child: it is not the traffic light's fault! The daycare catastrophe began with von der Leyen and the CDU/CSU have done nothing about it. And even in 2024, the Bavarian Minister of Social Affairs is shining with work refusal. At a great event that you can listen to on YouTube, "SOS daycare centers in Bavaria," you can hear which democratic parties are prepared to pull the cart out of the mud. Also interesting for people who do not have to live in Bavaria!

Der Syrien-Krieg war flÃ¼chtlingstechnisch eine wesentlich hÃ¶here Belastung. War aus meiner Sicht damals gut entschieden, aber schlecht gelenkt und gesteuert. Eine wirtschaftliche Belastung. Ja. With CDU and CSU on the way to a fascist system

During the Weimar Republic, many conservative circles saw the National Socialist German Workers' Party (NSDAP) as a potential force for restoring order and national strength. Figures such as Franz von Papen, a prominent conservative politician and former Chancellor, supported Adolf Hitler and helped him to come to power. They believed they could control Hitler and use him for their own purposes to overcome the democracy of the Weimar Republic and establish an authoritarian government.

However, this strategy proved fatal. After Hitler's appointment as Chancellor in January 1933 and the subsequent seizure of power, the NSDAP quickly established a totalitarian dictatorship.

The fact remains that many German conservatives, through their initial support and collaboration with the NSDAP, contributed significantly to the seizure of power and thus indirectly to the outbreak of World War II. The conservative forces are repeating their mistakes from that time.
